During a walk out through the Commonlands with his mother, a boy discovers a &quot;new place&quot; far rom his immaculate housing in the Temple of Marr of Freeport.<br>
<br>
&quot;Son, come back.  That land is riled with evil.&quot; spoke a pure but distressed voice.<br>
<br>
&quot;Heheheh, you can't stop me, heheheh.&quot; returned a fun-loving, chilidish boy.<br>
<br>
&quot;Cronatos, that is the land of the Tier'dal, our enemy.  If they find you...&quot;<br>
<br>
But by now, the boy was too deep in the forest.  He followed a small path to a bridge.  This is when Cronatos saw his first live Tier'dal, if you could call it &quot;seeing&quot; through this darkness.<br>
<br>
&quot;Foul human chilid!  We know who you are.  You fate shall be decided by the King himself.&quot; spoke the Tier'dal who seemed to see Cronatos as if it was perfect daylight.<br>
<br>
By now, Cronatos had lost consciousness with fright.  Although he was spared then, he couldn't shake the fear of imminent destruction, as so he fainted.<br>
<br>
&quot;Here is the boy.&quot;  announced the Tier'dal guard, dopping Cronatos on the ground.<br>
<br>
&quot;Excellant, our Lord shall be most pleased.&quot; the Tier'dal King told all present causing confusion amongst the crowd that expected the boy to be slain.<br>
<br>
Awaking from his unconscious nap, Cronatos squinted to see he was in the city of the Tier'dal, Neriak.  What startled the boy more was to see the King of this city on his throne of bone and flesh.<br>
<br>
&quot;Child, our Lord has called you down here as one of the few chosen to be one of His Dark Knights.  It has been decreed that you shall go back to Freeport, but not to the foul Temple of Marr... no.  You shall go to the slums of Freeport, under which is the temple devoted to Hate.  You are to study under Pietro Zarn.  NOW GO, my patience is wavering.&quot; the Tier'dal King told the shaking boy.<br>
<br>
-----<br>
<br>
&quot;These may be the &quot;chosen few&quot; but they are still just weak children...&quot; Pietro Zarn said with a sigh upon the first glance of Cronatos.<br>
<br>
Three days had passed before the spies in the Temple of Marr discovered Cronatos was under the arm of Pietro Zarn, leader of the ShadowKnight guild of Freeport.  Within minutes, Cronatos's mother appeared among both Pietro and Cronatos.<br>
<br>
&quot;Give me back my chilid, fool.&quot; the mother, now dressed in heavy pearlisecent platemail, yelled towards Pietro Zarn, who was dining on a small piece of dry bread at the time.<br>
<br>
&quot;He is one of us now.  Yet, I will still let him make the choice.&quot; Pietro rebutted.<br>
<br>
Cronatos then disappeared in a flash of blue bubble like forms.  Upon reappearance, he was behind his mother.  He grabbed the bottom of her chin with one hand, lifting it upwards.  In his other he held a dagger, to which he stabbed into his mother's neck.<br>
<br>
&quot;Excellant... maybe this one has the potential...&quot; Pietro murmured silently to himself.<br>
